<doc id="287676" wikidata="Q7414568" url="?curid=287676" title="San Juan Children's Choir">
<text>The San Juan Children&#x27;s Choir (&quot;Coro de Niños de San Juan&quot; in Spanish) is a children&#x27;s choir from San Juan, Puerto Rico. The group was founded in 1966 by its director, Evy Lucío Córdova.
The choir usually accepts participants from the age of 6 onwards. Auditions are held every year. Singers who are accepted at this institution leave around the age of 17 or 18.

The &quot;San Juan Children&#x27;s Choir&quot; has performed in many countries.
The choir performed at the second inauguration of Barack Obama.

